latestPosts.caption:
We won!!! 🏆,I can’t believe I’m officially the Cosmopolitan Artistic Makeup Artist of the Year 2024!!! My first ever cosmo nomination and my first award .Not even gonna lie, I had a tiny pic of this trophy on my vision board, and here we are—manifestation + hard work = this moment.

Let me be honest I lowkey felt like I was gonna win though, cause I knew I poured my heart and soul into every single content that I delivered this year. Strategy, creativity, and dedication were the secret and it’s all paying off. 💯

This win’s a big ol’ “thank you” to everyone who ever doubted me, especially those who told my fam I wasn’t doing a “real job.” Guess what? I’m out here creating something way bigger than that. 🙌🏼

Huge shoutout to my parents and friends who’ve been my constant support. 

Thankyou @ankursinghnitwal for styling me for my special day and handling my last minute stress also  @khualboi_thawmte for making this dress😍And a MASSIVE thank you to @cosmoindia for seeing and honoring my talent. This is just the beginning! 💫 
Captured by the amazing @dsdemoments 

#Grateful #ManifestationWorks #ArtisticMakeupArtistOfTheYear #cosmobloggerawards2024 #cosmoawards #makeup #award2024 #bloggersaward

latestPosts.caption:
METAMORPHOSIS.
the metamorphosis of a caterpillar into a butterfly  represents the idea of personal transformation and growth. It suggests that, like the caterpillar, we may need to undergo a period of intense self-reflection and personal development in order to reach our full potential.

The butterfly is often seen as a symbol of beauty, freedom, and rebirth, it is a symbol of renewal and new beginnings. It reminds us that even when things seem dark and difficult, there is always the potential for growth and change, and that we have the power to transform ourselves and our lives.
.
